document.title: Physical Education and Health Curriculum Framework (K-8)

B6A0B78251ED4A90947FAD0F1D63ED1D.description: Recognize that foods are categorized into groups (Refer to USDA)

8130BE4BBE9546039496B2F14D1A4E8F.description: Tell the importance of choosing healthy foods

C15B5C6B7CA84F4A8CF55899C2E56B9E.description: Identify healthy and unhealthy snacks and drinks

84E3E939F1D3465FA683ECBEC14B88AE.description: Nutrition: Students shall understand concepts related to nutrition and develop skills for making healthy food choices.

C0F51D52DE2B42B5A9AF1A888C41FE0B.description: Identify various behaviors associated with abuse, bullying, violence, and injury

E1AD020B929049438CC300CE6F06DC54.description: Identify sources to report abuse, bullying, violence, and injury
comments: (e.g., teachers, nurses, counselor, ministers, parents, coaches)

0358DFD9B2344A83A6BCC5A2012FD77D.description:
Practice safety rules pertaining to threatening strangers:
  • shout, kick or scream
  • tell an adult
  • avoid stranger's vehicle

7B89DAC1F0ED43309EE76208652C8D35.description: Understand how to get help in an emergency

E092F68F6DAA4F6CBFC416EAA01062D8.description: Discuss safety procedures for lifetime activities

E2674D033EEE464A89FA3012F866665F.description: Discuss the role of the dentist and dental hygienist

ECAB1E3A749C47E6800E874610DEFEC9.description: Understand the difference between primary teeth and permanent teeth

40F2F1932B9B43A0915B34EF081EE918.description: Name trusted adults to notify for help

35214782C9334186A4EE073BEC68D002.description: Recognize good and bad choices for coping

comments: (e.g., happy, sad, excited, afraid, surprised, angry, embarrassed, proud)

2ABD05FFFE4045A88A4730CA30ED2A9E.description: Personal Health and Safety: Students shall recognize and practice health-enhancing behaviors to reduce health risks.

11006291FD374A77940F6D277E81F59D.description: Recognize ways to avoid tobacco, drug, and alcohol use
comments: (e.g., say "NO", ignore, walk away, a better idea)

3908DBCF99CD415381B618BDD585980A.description: Recognize that some drugs are illegal

E18AFA1D50FD4A0A98725466B4855E8C.description: Recognize that alcohol is a drug

69E45134783740A49058188A5D391568.description: Recognize the effects of tobacco products on the body

5187540CA5CB4BCB9B93569EBB4135EA.description: Identify reliable adults to dispense medicines

8F984D49C95C48789CE949555316DEAE.description: Name basic rules for taking medicine

F617D8DFEECC4CBF86A9AB85EE4D58E1.description: Alcohol, Tobacco, and Other Drugs: Students shall comprehend substance use, abuse, and the ability to use decision-making skills to enhance health.

E6546E40A88B498F8286DF67A96F2497.description: Identify characteristics that make a good friend

8473C79B067842A88459C0A484ED899A.description: Identify positive and negative ways to get attention

74F9E9ACB45149AAB150D8BA6B8BF064.description: Healthy Life Skills and Relationships: Students shall demonstrate the ability to use appropriate skills to enhance relationships and promote wellness.

BADA98282CDA4FF5A655E79B61F59E24.description:
Discuss community health care providers:
  • doctor
  • dentist
  • community health department
  • school nurse
  • counselor

C8DB1A5E6B194C6BA06373B2EF82B913.description: Community Health and Promotion: Students shall demonstrate the ability to access valid health information, products, and services that promote consumer, community, and environmental health.

A56D103B4D074FF38FC6C32C17C8C7A9.description:
List methods of protection from illness:
  • wash hands
  • cover sneeze/cough
  • immunization (shots)

537C08A63E7C4E2D9FE6DA811090E17C.description: Disease Prevention: Students shall understand components related to disease prevention and exhibit behaviors to promote health.

43602927F2C1475AB3C4389849079711.description: Recognize different physical characteristics of an individual

32A5D16E8B674149A23DE8D4E5558EC5.description:
Name and locate the following body parts:
  • heart
  • lungs
  • brain
  • stomach
  • muscles
  • bones

8BCE913838E9489C8D515528A12CC7B9.description: Human Growth and Development Students shall understand characteristics relating to growth and development.

499E3E0CB5144F549D94BD55D76D5C3B.description: Use and share equipment within personal space safely and properly

F02B115305CC486B9029C6757CE9CE5D.description: Identify acceptable behaviors while participating in physical activities
comments: (e.g., not quitting on the first attempt, taking turns, etc.)

E18B0AAA58D44DCB8707E5D7CF46C255.description: Personal and Social Behavior: Students shall demonstrate responsible personal and social behavior that respects self and others in physical activity settings.

comments: (e.g., fishing, bird watching, hiking, camping, golf, running)
44490A1B5C4244949CDA5D3026065848.description: Recognize a variety of lifetime physical activities

24A348AAD3D84EA1A22F4AD7D2CCCD27.description: Recognize that exercise takes place during active play and builds a healthy heart and lungs

406DA541F590408D9149B34ACE8C1456.description: Lifetime Activities and Recreation: Students shall understand the importance of health benefits and enjoyment from participating in lifetime recreational activities.

5772FBA6A9794A7A9EE8A03C0C6BD105.description:
Participate in a nationally recognized health-fitness assessment:
  • cardiorespiratory endurance
  • body composition
  • muscular strength and endurance
  • flexibility

DC9109BE453D49088135E8FBBD4FBB30.description: Practice appropriate activities to improve muscular endurance

55C0C2ED7C3E43BC8A80F33C322C7FEC.description: Understand the importance of participating in daily moderate to vigorous physical activity

comments: (e.g., pull-ups, push-ups, modified push-ups, plank, flex arm hang)
(e.g., animal walk, scooter activities, push up and hold)

69689F2998C64DD69E3D1A3A42D2EF4E.description:
Participate in stretching activities that improve flexibility:
  • dynamic warm up
  • teacher-led stretching held for a short period of time without bouncing

DCE5EBB3E8F1491F888174BAE138E6B9.description: Recognize that the body is capable of a wide range of movement

414E20B17CB1457EAE3D6FF78099ECA4.description: Understand that the body needs proper nutrition and water to function

D8F72CCC67A8454287643AB38A74E888.description: Understand that the body is composed of muscles and bones

B45F170FDE0648BEA4E17907DF179049.description: Participate in an age-appropriate activity, exercise, or game that encourages pacing to develop cardiorespiratory endurance

6E1929E4C6AD4FD2AB95AC5223B89F4F.description: Recognize the change in breathing and heart beat while participating in a moderate to vigorous activity

4F4BAC219D654249BC52BF6A7C5CBA72.description: Know that the heart functions as a pump for blood

5D4E2F1AF4CF4D7D90DA445641BEA2FF.description: Locate the heart and understand that it is the size of a fist

A9C3DA934C484BECB0A91E999DE9045C.description: Health-Related Fitness: Students shall understand how health-related fitness can improve individual health.

CF5C70D6AAA34256A8B9A9A82B8AF254.description:
Know that the body and brain need activity for optimal function:
  • oxygen to the brain
  • ability to focus

40F4519987B84AA59C99ABF58B56289F.description: Participate in loworganized games that utilize basic motor skills

5A1A2771668A46668576A93949191497.description:
Identify lower body parts:
  • hip, thigh, calf, heel, ankles, knees, right foot, left foot, leg, toes

CFC037EDACEC41658D2E94BB44C8B1E9.description:
Identify upper body parts:
  • head
  • forehead
  • chin
  • chest
  • eyes, ears, nose, mouth,
  • shoulders, arm, neck, elbows, wrist, right hand, left hand, fingers
  • back, waist, stomach

70DAA9E339934D8D9D9FFB1BF3D8BE32.description: Movement Concepts: Students shall understand movement concepts, principles, and strategies that apply to the performance of physical activity.

8CF7E4E881BA4D83BD67E18BAA4D5095.description: Trap a moving ball with the foot

70B17FA6B23B454DB923E4A5A84966F9.description: Use limited body movement when kicking with the dominant leg

87C308A06B1B4CEE9C87505B91950DEF.description: Move a ball with the feet

7FE96B6287C1402FAF2626EE463953B4.description: Volley a balloon with the hands

60CF41C448E4436B969597BE56567476.description: Use limited body movement when striking an object using the dominant arm

AC1FDFA9EED3470E9A545E3A01BB43EA.description: Bounce a ball using one or two hands in self-space and general space

E5FFBA85F05A41BDB24B35D4D12A8FC7.description: Extend arms toward thrower when catching an object

566A50492075430B880FDA77381D2DCA.description: Use limited body movement when throwing with the dominant arm

F1CCE452D6E54F47A630A8FFB07D8863.description: Travel to a beat by marching, clapping, and stomping with a fast and slow pace, using even and uneven rhythm

12E2A42580BB4823B5C86E4FB9737872.description:
Perform the following non-locomotor movements:
  • balance
  • bend
  • stretch
  • turn
  • twist
  • shake
  • cross-lateral (crossing the mid-line of the body)
  • push
  • pull
  • sway

057E29DEBFDD4C12A78B2EA732509C10.description: Move appropriately in general space within boundaries without falling down and bumping into others

A35CBA362777405E957C60953178F4C5.description: Move forward, side-to-side, high/medium/low, stop/go, under, over, behind, beside, and through

322FC22CB9E74401A7CFFF07A542E342.description: Demonstrate dynamic and static movements, and dynamic and static balance using various body positions

3BA022A245F643BBA8AC3A916B3A1BA9.description: Motor Skills and Movement Patterns: Students shall demonstrate proficiency in motor skills and movement patterns needed to perform a variety of activities.
